TopicTitle: Kerbal Space Program: First Contract Now Available

Articles.Content:
<p><img alt="image" src="https://31.media.tumblr.com/cf6039a8e29b693eed06bd3bb8d60aad/tumblr_inline_n8rm1lBjkL1rr2wit.jpg"/></p>

<p><em>Kerbal Space Program</em>, the award-winning, indie space agency sim game from <strong>Squad</strong>, is launching its latest update, <em>Kerbal Space Program: First Contract</em>, as part of its active development cycle. This major release, numbered 0.24, is a substantial advancement in the game’s Career Mode, which challenges players to run a space agency.<span><span> It is also the first time the gameoffersa</span></span> a <strong>64-bit version for Windows</strong> via <strong><a href="http://bit.ly/1fUQQjy" target="_blank">STEAM</a></strong> and the <strong><a href="http://bit.ly/1jQTSlj" target="_blank"><em>KSP</em> STORE</a></strong>.</p>

<p>Read more about <em>Kerbal Space Program: First Contract</em> <a href="http://bit.ly/1skqSdD"><strong>HERE</strong></a> and <a href="http://bit.ly/1l0npcD"><strong>HERE</strong></a>.</p>

Parse error: syntax error, unexpected end of file in /host/www.kerbalspaceprogram.com/htdocs/lib/multiplayDwn.php on line 132

As a freelance web developer, I can say that this isn't a result of an overloaded server. The PHP script itself is trying to execute a non-existent part of the script. It usually happens under two conditions: the code is at the end of the file, but isn't closed; or the server isn't done executing the script when it hits the close tag.
